Drug/Laboratory Test Interferences: Dicu-marol and indanedione anticoagulants, including anisindione, or their metabolites may color alkaline urine red-orange, which may interfere with spectrophotometrically determined urinary laboratory tests.
The color reverses when the test sample is acidified in vitro to a pH below 4.
